The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Luxury hotels for tourists
                                                                                                               Luxury hotels for tourists
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Patna, March 17: Bihars tourism department has decided to open a five-star hotel in Patna and upgrade existing guesthouses in an attempt to boost tourism.         
	States tourism minister Nandkishore Yadav confirmed the news today before the media. Hotels in Rajgir and Bodh Gaya are especially slated for the makeover magic  since these two places are popular destinations for people who belong to Jain and Buddhist communities. The plan to start a five-star hotel in Patna and upgrade others have been sent to the chief ministers office (CMO) for final approval, said a tourism department official, adding: The CMO is likely to grant a positive response soon.        
	The department plans to upgrade Tathagat Vihar in Rajgir and Siddhartha Vihar in Bodh Gaya to three-star status, while starting a convention centre and a championship golf course in Bodh Gaya.        
	Provision to open a rest house for the Kanwaria community at Sultanganj and Rampur has been made and the plan has been submitted by the tourism department to the CMO, said the official.        
	The government has sent eight schemes to the Centre for its approval to open a cultural complex in Bodh Gaya, a cultural village in Nalanda, and a food and craft institute in Muzaffarpur among others, at the cost of Rs 74 crore.                                                                                                                                                                           
